Got it! We'll focus on making the **menu UI for graph selection** look cleaner and more user-friendly on pages like **Product** and **Trade**, without touching the sidebar for now.

Let’s modernize the menu with a neat design using just plain CSS (since Bootstrap is no longer being used). Here’s a suggested version with a dropdown or button group approach:

---

### ✅ Step-by-step: Improved Graph Selection Menu (Plain CSS)

#### 1. **Menu HTML Code** (inside your Product.razor or Trade.razor page):

```razor
<h3 class="section-title">Select Graph to Display</h3>

<div class="graph-menu">
    <button @onclick="() => SelectedGraph = 'otcProductTypes'" class="@GetButtonClass("otcProductTypes")">OTC Product Types</button>
    <button @onclick="() => SelectedGraph = 'bnabparProductTypes'" class="@GetButtonClass("bnabparProductTypes")">BNABPAR Product Types</button>
    <button @onclick="() => SelectedGraph = 'contractSource'" class="@GetButtonClass("contractSource")">Contracts by Source</button>
</div>

@if (SelectedGraph == "otcProductTypes")
{
    <ProductTradeChart />
}
else if (SelectedGraph == "bnabparProductTypes")
{
    <BnabparTradeChart />
}
else if (SelectedGraph == "contractSource")
{
    <ContractSourceChart />
}
```

#### 2. **Code Section**:

```razor
@code {
    private string SelectedGraph = "otcProductTypes";

    private string GetButtonClass(string key) =>
        key == SelectedGraph ? "graph-btn active" : "graph-btn";
}
```

#### 3. **CSS Styling** (add this in `wwwroot/css/site.css` or scoped CSS):

```css
.graph-menu {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.graph-btn {
    padding: 0.5rem 1.2rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    border: 2px solid #ddd;
    border-radius: 6px;
    background: #f5f5f5;
    color: #333;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.2s ease-in-out;
}

.graph-btn:hover {
    background: #e0e0e0;
}

.graph-btn.active {
    background: #4a90e2;
    color: white;
    border-color: #4a90e2;
}
```

---

### ✅ Result:
- Looks minimal, modern, and matches most UI themes.
- Very lightweight – no external libraries.
- Easily extendable with more graph components later.

---

